rules.natural: If the Endangered Species Project receives research funding, then research findings data get published
If the Endangered Species Project receives research funding, then the Wildlife Rescue Center maintains operational status

If satellite platform monitoring becomes established, then should the research program experience increased funding, then whenever rescue teams of volunteers become mobilized, endangered species animals are rescued
Either rare species breeding proves successful or protected area habitat becomes restored
If protected area habitat becomes restored, then Wildlife Project conservation goals become achieved
If poaching activity remains high in the protected zone, then endangered species population does not show declining trends
If ecosystem habitat degradation becomes severe, then endangered species population does not show declining trends
If government grant funding gets cut, then the Wildlife Rescue Center facility does not close
Either government grant funding gets cut or public support for conservation efforts remains low
If media coverage of the rescue facility turns negative, then under the condition that public support for conservation efforts remains low, the Wildlife Rescue Center facility does not close
If legal action gets taken against poachers, then poaching ring arrests get made
Either legal action gets taken against poachers or endangered species population does not show declining trends
If rare species show recovery progress, then Wildlife Project conservation goals become achieved
If the government grant receives approval, then should the Wildlife Rescue Center maintain operational status, Wildlife Project conservation goals become achieved
Either the government grant receives approval or a major conservancy organization provides donations
If a major conservancy organization provides donations, then provided that the Wildlife Rescue Center maintains operational status, Wildlife Project conservation goals become achieved
If the public awareness app platform launches successfully, then Wildlife Project conservation goals become achieved
Either the public awareness app platform launches successfully or rescue teams of volunteers become mobilized
If endangered species animals are rescued, then Wildlife Project conservation goals become achieved
Either the research program experiences increased funding or a corporate sponsor forms a partnership
If a corporate sponsor forms a partnership, then under the condition that rescue teams of volunteers become mobilized, endangered species animals are rescued
If rare species breeding proving successful does not result in rare species showing recovery progress, then UN Program international aid gets requested
If rare species breeding proving successful does not cause rare species to show recovery progress, then Consortium emergency funding does not become activated
If rare species breeding proving successful fails to lead to Wildlife Project conservation goals becoming achieved, then endangered species population shows declining trends
If neither poaching activity remains high in the protected zone nor ecosystem habitat degradation becomes severe, then species conservation status shows improvement
If research findings data getting published does not result in Wildlife Project conservation goals becoming achieved, then the Wildlife Rescue Center facility closes
If legal action getting taken against poachers does not lead to poaching ring arrests not getting made, then conservation laws court case remains pending
If legal action getting taken against poachers does not cause poaching ring arrests to not get made, then conservation laws court case does not remain pending
If UN Program international aid getting requested does not trigger Consortium emergency funding becoming activated, then the rescue center facility undergoes expansion
